* She kept her eyes on him at all times, never taking them from him...or 
blinking either.
If he suddenly moved towards her, she wanted to see it.
But with no slight muscle twitches or any movemnt at all, she was doubtful 
he was going to try anything.

She heard his words but her logical robotic mind was beginning to lose what 
little control it had, which meant that soon she would only be running on 
instincts.
Which wouldn't be good at all for Prowl.
Because her instincts saw him as nothing but one thing...lunch.

But for now, he was safe...somewhat.
She stopped her pacing and took in the meaning of what Prowl was saying, 
almost as if she could actually consider doing what he asked...but she knew 
she couldn't.

Though, she knew that soon she would be just as mean as before, and that she 
somehow had to get out of there...NOW!
Her eyes shifting from Prowl and locking on the door behind him, moving 
slowly step by step...not towards Prowl...but the door.
Suddenly, without warning she suddenly heaved her muscles and whisked by 
Prowl, slamming a muscle bulked shoulder into the metal seal of the door.
Backing away to reviel a dent, but then ramming right into it again.
She had to get out, before she hurt him again!*
